    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="775"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/2305a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3510. You may, at the request to us of interested Jewish groups in the United
                    States, make a <hi rend="italic">pro forma</hi> inquiry of the Foreign Office as
                    to the veracity of reports which have been received by Jewish circles from Syria
                    to the effect that the British authorities in Palestine will not permit 1700
                    refugees of German and Austrian origin to land from a Greek ship now off the
                    Palestine coast and are suggesting that they proceed to Mauritius.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
